The paper discusses adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a binary classifier approach to distinguish between adversarial and clean data, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
